The really easy way is to just map 0-15 to -2048 through 2048 by multiplying and adding.  Don't forget to interpolate, as even linear interpolation sounds a great deal better than no interpolation.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Mon Dec 08, 2008 6:32 am</p><hr />
